"""
excel_to_email.py  (pandas version — no openpyxl required)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
REPLACES: snowflake_extract.py  (when DB is not updated / manual data entry)

HOW IT WORKS:
  1. User fills in  delay_input.xlsx  with the required columns
  2. pandas reads the Excel into a DataFrame  (uses the xlrd / openpyxl engine
     that ships with pandas — no separate install needed in most IDPs)
  3. Each DataFrame row is fed into the email template and sent via Amazon SES

DEPENDENCIES (all standard in most IDP environments):
  pandas, boto3   — no openpyxl needed directly

RUN:
  python excel_to_email.py                          # uses delay_input.xlsx
  python excel_to_email.py --file my_data.xlsx      # custom file
  python excel_to_email.py --dry-run                # preview without sending
  python excel_to_email.py --sheet "Sheet2"         # pick a specific sheet
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
"""

